      "anchor_proposed": {
        "vr_id": 130834,
        "reference": "Gen 15:6",
        "strongs": "H2803H",
        "translit": "cha.shav",
        "anchor_rationale": "'And he believed the Lord, and he counted it to him as righteousness.' The foundational imputation verse. The inner act — God's crediting of Abraham's faith as righteousness — is stated with complete simplicity. This verse anchors the entire evaluative-reckoning phenomenon and is the most theologically significant instance in the group."
      }
