      "anchor_proposed": {
        "vr_id": 130886,
        "reference": "Psa 73:16",
        "strongs": "H2803J",
        "translit": "cha.shav",
        "anchor_rationale": "'But when I thought how to understand this, it seemed to me a wearisome task.' The deliberate inner effort to form a judgment about a difficult reality — the prosperity of the wicked — is named in its most honest and effortful form. Thinking is presented as work: sustained inner cognitive attending that produces weariness before producing resolution (which only comes in the sanctuary, v.17)."
      }
