    {
      "code": "M15-D-VCG05",
      "label": "Taste as inner discernment faculty (ta.am)",
      "context_description": "The term names tasting as the figure for inner discernment — the palate that tests food becomes the image for the inner faculty that tests words, situations, and God himself. Includes literal tasting (Jonathan's honey, Nineveh's fast, mourning abstinence), and figurative tasting (taste and see that the Lord is good; the ear tests words as the palate tastes food). Inner-being phenomenon: taste as the organ of inner discernment.",
