      "anchor_proposed": {
        "vr_id": 155374,
        "reference": "Psa 34:8",
        "strongs": "H2938",
        "translit": "ta.am",
        "anchor_rationale": "'Oh, taste and see that the Lord is good! Blessed is the man who takes refuge in him.' The most explicit use of taste as the figure for inner spiritual discernment. The command to taste God's goodness is a command to exercise the inner faculty of discernment directly on the person of God. The verse makes clear what the whole group implies: inner discernment is a form of personal testing by direct contact."
      }
