    {
      "code": "M15-D-VCG06",
      "label": "Prudent cunning — the double-edged inner disposition (a.rum/a.rom)",
      "context_description": "The term names the inner quality of shrewd perceptiveness that can be either wisdom or cunning depending on its direction. The serpent is crafty (a.rum) — the same word that describes the prudent person who sees danger and hides, conceals knowledge, and gives thought to steps. The phenomenon is a sharp, discerning inner disposition that either serves wisdom or serves deception. Inner-being phenomenon: shrewd inner discernment as double-edged disposition.",
