        "reference": "Gen 3:1",
        "strongs": "H6175",
        "translit": "a.rum",
        "anchor_rationale": "'Now the serpent was more crafty than any other beast of the field.' This is the first use of a.rum and it immediately establishes the double-edged nature of the inner disposition: the same word that Proverbs will apply to the prudent person appears here for the deceiving serpent. The word holds both valences simultaneously, and this verse — the initial use — names the darker one with perfect economy."
