    {
      "code": "M15-D-VCG07",
      "label": "Inner arguments and conflicting thoughts (logismos)",
      "context_description": "The term names the cognitive argumentation of the inner person — thoughts that accuse or excuse before the conscience, and mental strongholds opposed to God that must be taken captive. The phenomenon is inner cognitive contention: the thought-life as a site of argument and resistance. Inner-being phenomenon: inner conflicting or resistive thoughts.",
