      "anchor_proposed": {
        "vr_id": 101921,
        "reference": "Rom 2:15",
        "strongs": "G3053",
        "translit": "logismos",
        "anchor_rationale": "'Their conflicting thoughts accuse or even excuse them.' The most direct statement of the phenomenon: thoughts (logismoi) that operate within the inner person as a dual court — accusing and defending before the conscience. The word names not a single thought but the entire inner argumentation that constitutes moral self-awareness."
      }
